### Instruction:
Create an algorithm for optimizing a dataset by replacing missing values with the median of the dataset.

### Response:
// Function to replace missing with median
double replaceMissingWithMedian(double[] arr, int n)
{
 // Create a temporary array
 double temp[n];

 // Copy all valid values from arr[] to temp[]
 int j = 0;
 for (int i=0; i < n; i++)
 {
	 if (arr[i] != 'null')
		 temp[j++] = arr[i];
 }

 // Sort the temp array
 sort(temp, j);

 // Find the median
 // If number of elements is odd,
 // return the middle element
 if (j%2 == 1)
	 return (temp[j/2]);

 // If number of elements is even,
 // return mean of middle two elements
 return (temp[(j-1)/2] + temp[j/2])/2.0;
}

// Replace missing with median
for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
 if (arr[i] == 'null')
	 arr[i] = replaceMissingWithMedian(arr, n);

### Instruction:
Develop an algorithm for finding the longest consecutive sequence of 1s in an integer array.

### Response:
def longest_ones_sequence (arr):
    curr_length = 0
    max_length = 0
    for i in range(len(arr)):
        if arr[i] == 1:
            curr_length += 1
            if curr_length > max_length:
                max_length = curr_length
        else:
            curr_length = 0
    return max_length

